'''''Starlog'' Salutes ''Star Wars''''' also known as '''''Star Wars''''' '''10th anniversary convention''' was the first officially sponsored ''[[Star Wars]]'' convention. It was "A 10th Anniversary Tribute to George Lucas and the Galaxy Far, Far Away Which He Created," held at the Stouffer Concourse Hotel in [[Wikipedia:Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles, California]] from [[May 23]] to [[May 25]], [[1987]].<ref name="Empire Turns 40">{{ThisWeek|6UccH037VQ0|The Empire Strikes Back Turns 40, Queen's Peril Gets a Voice, and More!}}</ref> It was organized by ''Starlog Magazine'' and Creation Conventions.<ref name="lfcm">[[The Lucasfilm Fan Club Magazine 1|''The Lucasfilm Fan Club Magazine'' 1]]</ref> [[George Lucas]] attended. [[Wikipedia:Gene Roddenberry|Gene Roddenberry]], the creator of [[Memoryalpha:Star Trek|''Star Trek'']], was a surprise guest; this resulted in the only known photograph of him with Lucas being taken by [[Dan Madsen]].<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.trekcore.com/specials/tenforward/article5|text=Dan Madsen: Star Trek's Fan Communicator|author=Tenuto, John|date=2007-10-14|archivedate=20120822222119}}</ref>

